    {
      "id": "KhzvhzIxLbmAijYpxeY27",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 181.16711973799931,
      "y": 1541.9789834365822,
      "width": 747,
      "height": 260,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#000000",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "cRbG",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 376563847,
      "version": 386,
      "versionNonce": 748581270,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768568188278,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Cassandra is the chosen DB for event storage\nBecause of its capability for very high write throughput\nbuilt-in distribution and partitioning, no single point of failure in the cluster\nIt doesn't have isolation between the different transactions, but that's fine for event storage\n\ntable: outbox_events\n - partition_key (for even distribution)\n - created_at\n - status (pending, sent, failed)\n - kafka_topic_name\n - raw_event text\n - event_id uuid\n - PRIMARY KEY (partition_key, created_at, event_id)",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Cassandra is the chosen DB for event storage\nBecause of its capability for very high write throughput\nbuilt-in distribution and partitioning, no single point of failure in the cluster\nIt doesn't have isolation between the different transactions, but that's fine for event storage\n\ntable: outbox_events\n - partition_key (for even distribution)\n - created_at\n - status (pending, sent, failed)\n - kafka_topic_name\n - raw_event text\n - event_id uuid\n - PRIMARY KEY (partition_key, created_at, event_id)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "XFNuulwbcmzPVjqA3vbQW",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -176.25790380520345,
      "y": 1843.8122049126832,
      "width": 1008.6749877929688,
      "height": 140,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#000000",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "cRbH",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1295331817,
      "version": 1329,
      "versionNonce": 1206622922,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1768568188278,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "We have separate logic applying the Outbox pattern, essentially we store the raw data for every event.\nThen we have an outbox job that polls the raw events from the DB and republishes them to the \ncorrect topic. This is done to avoid Kafka as a single point of failure.\nCurrently if Kafka goes down we will have data loss and miss events, this event storage is the solution to that problem.\nThe only problem is that the consumers will have one extra idempotency hit, because we'll publish the same event twice to topic\nand only that adds extra overhead to Kafka. Currently the job will run every few minutes take everything from the DB and push \nit to the topics then change the status of the events to \"sent\".",
      "fontSize": 16,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "We have separate logic applying the Outbox pattern, essentially we store the raw data for every event.\nThen we have an outbox job that polls the raw events from the DB and republishes them to the \ncorrect topic. This is done to avoid Kafka as a single point of failure.\nCurrently if Kafka goes down we will have data loss and miss events, this event storage is the solution to that problem.\nThe only problem is that the consumers will have one extra idempotency hit, because we'll publish the same event twice to topic\nand only that adds extra overhead to Kafka. Currently the job will run every few minutes take everything from the DB and push \nit to the topics then change the status of the events to \"sent\".",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
